  "body": "when we run kube-down.sh to move a k8s cluster, we want a clean env to deploy a new cluster next time. https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/pull/12075. we need to move all remains, includes volumes of pod. https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/pull/12704\nHowever, if we can add a command like \"kubectl remove all pods\", or  let Kubelet clean up volumes. It is better than writing script.\nSo i want to add a new command to remove all mount volumes, before kube-down a cluster.\n",
